					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13896591#post-4838362</guid>
				<title>Glad That I Decided to Keep Reading</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13896591/scp-5083#post-4838362</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Mon, 07 Dec 2020 03:32:39 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>MindlessPhilosopher</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>7085649</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>When I first started reading this, I was like &quot;yeah, a gold man that you eat, and you get gold delivered, and then the Foundation gets mean, and takes it away. Meh.&quot;</p> <p>And then I started reading the transcripts, and I couldn't help but upvote.</p> <p>A lot of might be cliché and tropified (the car chase, the O5 council fighting over the Goldman), but then again, I don't mind cliché if done right. And I found a lot of the humor to be rather cheeky.</p> <p>The guy with a chainsaw and going &quot;Timbeeeer!&quot; was just classic, and helps set the tone! And I have to agree with Raptie. The line &quot;Aye&#8230; want to eat that gold man&quot; was just brilliant!</p> <p>The repeating fight between the O5 council comes off as a bit repetitive by the third incarnation, but the listing of a different set of weapons (apparently standard for the Foundation, though what the heck Switchback Energy Grenades, Zoological Grenades, Reverse Matter Railguns, and Occult Pistols and Rifles are supposed to is sadly still a mystery) was also interesting. And apparently, they also have farm animals scurrying around headquarters now&#8230;</p> <p>Having O5-4 dive through Alpha-1-5's legs was pretty funny, but I think that visually, having a couple of other O5's accidentally run into him like in Home Alone 2 would be hilarious!</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
