					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13896591#post-4838239</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13896591/scp-5083#post-4838239</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Sun, 06 Dec 2020 23:03:43 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Sputnik One</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>7005588</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>Hi Author, I've noticed a few typos.</p> <blockquote> <p>The current will be worth as much as the gold making up the consumed 5083-1's body.</p> </blockquote> <p>Should &quot;current&quot; here be currency? This sentence also doesn't read well (in my opinion). I think it'd be better phrased as:</p> <div class="collapsible-block"> <div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;show&nbsp;block</a></div> <div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none"> <div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">–&nbsp;hide&nbsp;block</a></div> <div class="collapsible-block-content"> <blockquote> <p><em>Individuals who have consumed portions of 5083-1 will receive a sum of currency<br /> proportional to the quantity of gold they ingested.</em></p> </blockquote> <hr /> <blockquote> <p>O5-11: (pauses) …Apolagies.</p> </blockquote> <hr /> <p>This is a really imaginative SCP, but the main problem I have with it (and why ultimately I decided on a neutral vote) is the reaction of the Overseer Council. In the description you state:</p> <blockquote> <p>Unless they have undergone at least Level 3 memetic agent resistance training, any<br /> further people that see 5083-1 after initial manifestation will gain the same desires<br /> to consume them.</p> </blockquote> <p>For me, I find it hard to believe that field agents and MTFs would have this memetic resistance training, but not the O5 Council. I know the O5s don't operate in the field, but they are, after all, the most important people within the Foundation, and not people you want compromised.</p> <hr /> <blockquote> <p>O5-4 runs towards Alpha-1-5, twists his face into a cognitohazardous facial expression</p> </blockquote> <p>I'm not sure what this is meant to mean? Are you saying O5-4 is contorting his face in a way that makes it a cognitohazard?</p> <hr /> <p>Ultimately, I was more interested in Operation Lifeboat than the skip itself. Moreover, I don't feel like Eunike 185 added anything to the story. In my opinion, if it was removed it it wouldn't change much (unless Operation Lifeboat and Eunike 185 are linked?)</p> </div> </div> </div> <p><em>As a courtesy to our readers on mobile devices, please collapse long posts. ~Zyn</em></p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
